                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/5309: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1930-06-30T10:20:00-04:00"
                            notBefore="1930-06-29T00:00:00+08:00">undated</date>].<lb/>[Received
                        June 30, 1930—10:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>520. Following from Reuter, Nanking, June 29: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The Customs Administration has ordered the customs at Chinwangtao, which
                            has heretofore been under the jurisdiction of the Tientsin customs, to
                            be immediately transferred and placed under the control of the
                            Shanhaikuan customs as a precautionary measure to prevent the
                            Chinwangtao customs from being seized and utilized by Marshal Yen
                            Hsi-shan.</p>
                        <p>The Navy Minister said that Marshal Chang Hsueh-liang has despatched the
                            gunboat <hi rend="italic">Tinghai</hi> belonging to the northeastern
                            (Manchurian) naval squadron to Chinwangtao to enforce the transfer.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
